returns._address: The address where the contract is deployed

getSyndicateFeeAddress().details: This function is needed to allow inheriting contracts to only be able to view but not change syndicateFeeAddress without going through ownerSetSyndicateFeeAddress

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.feeAddress: The owner's new contract fee address

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

contractAddress.details: Currently we store the data inside the logic contract. Once we feel comfortable with what data is needed by outside parties we will split this into separate contracts.

ownerSetSyndicateFeeAddress(address).notice: set a new fee address for the contract function that can only be triggered by the contract owner.

ownerTransferOwnership(address).notice: Transfers ownership to the provided address.
